I have 10 Oracle tables used for DQ/PARCM failures. Each of the 10 tables currently contains both core failure columns and comment/metadata columns. I need to restructure them so that:

1. All 10 failure tables keep ONLY the core failure columns (columns 3–18).

2. The following comment/metadata columns must be removed from every failure table:
	•	INCLUDED_EXCLUDE
	•	EXCLUSION_TYPE
	•	ADDITIONAL_FAILURE_COMMENTS
	•	FAILURE_STATUS
	•	TECHADS_JIRA_STORY
	•	JIRA_STORY_CREATION_DATE
	•	JIRA_STORY_FIX_DATE
	•	FILE_NAME
	•	INSERT_DTM

(These are the columns highlighted in my SLA_DQ DDL screenshot. Note: the existing column is FILE_NAME, not USER_NAME.)

3. A new 11th table must be created to store these removed columns plus:
	•	FAILURE_ID – numeric foreign key from the failure tables
	•	COMMENT_ID – numeric primary key generated by the application
	•	USER_NAME – the name of the user who made the update

4. Add a new column to each failure table:

FAILURE_ID  NUMBER

(Autosys will populate this.)

⸻

What I want you to generate

A. ALTER TABLE scripts (for all 10 failure tables)

For each table:
	1.	ALTER TABLE <table_name> ADD FAILURE_ID NUMBER;
	2.	ALTER TABLE <table_name> DROP COLUMN <column_to_remove>;

Repeat the DROP COLUMN for each of these columns:
	•	INCLUDED_EXCLUDE
	•	EXCLUSION_TYPE
	•	ADDITIONAL_FAILURE_COMMENTS
	•	FAILURE_STATUS
	•	TECHADS_JIRA_STORY
	•	JIRA_STORY_CREATION_DATE
	•	JIRA_STORY_FIX_DATE
	•	FILE_NAME
	•	INSERT_DTM

Output a full ALTER script for all 10 tables. I will provide the list of table names separately, so use clear placeholders like <TABLE_1>, <TABLE_2>, etc.

⸻

B. CREATE TABLE script for the new comments/metadata table

Table name:

CONTROLS_TECHADS_METRICS.FAILURE_COMMENTS

Columns:
	•	COMMENT_ID                  NUMBER              – primary key, generated by UI
	•	FAILURE_ID                  NUMBER              – FK to failure tables
	•	INCLUDED_EXCLUDE            VARCHAR2(1000 BYTE)
	•	EXCLUSION_TYPE              VARCHAR2(1000 BYTE)
	•	ADDITIONAL_FAILURE_COMMENTS VARCHAR2(1000 BYTE)
	•	FAILURE_STATUS              VARCHAR2(1000 BYTE)
	•	TECHADS_JIRA_STORY          VARCHAR2(1000 BYTE)
	•	JIRA_STORY_CREATION_DATE    DATE
	•	JIRA_STORY_FIX_DATE         DATE
	•	FILE_NAME                   VARCHAR2(1000 BYTE)
	•	USER_NAME                   VARCHAR2(200 BYTE)
	•	INSERT_DTM                  DATE

Constraints:
	•	Primary key on COMMENT_ID
	•	Foreign key: FAILURE_ID references the FAILURE_ID column in the failure tables (use a placeholder FK definition and comment where the target table should be specified, since multiple failure tables will reference this table).

⸻

C. Output format
	•	Provide clean, executable Oracle SQL scripts.
	•	Group the ALTER TABLE statements by table.
	•	Provide the CREATE TABLE script at the end.
	•	Use Oracle syntax only.
	•	Do not add extra commentary or explanations; just the SQL.
